  "time_ut": 1658748344,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d91\u0dc5\u0dc0\u0dc5\u0dd4 \u0db4\u0dd0\u0dc5\u0dad\u0dca \u0d9c\u0dab\u0db1\u0dca \u0d8b\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dc3\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Vegetables are high",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "It is reported that the prices of plants such as vegetables and chillies required for cultivation have also increased.",
        "Especially in Colombo and the suburbs, the price of chillies, kochi, tomatoes, cabbage, brinjal etc. has increased between 50 and 100 rupees per plant.",
        "In a place selling vegetable plants in Colombo city, the price of a plant like chili, fish chili, Varaniya chili is 100 rupees, the price of a tomato plant is 75 rupees and the price of a green cabbage plant is 80 rupees.",
        "Vegetable plants are also sold in Gampaha town at a price of 60 rupees per plant. A plant shop in Boralasgamuwa area sells a plant of chillies, tomatoes, eggplants etc. at the price of 50 rupees.",
        "A plant nursery in Piliyandala area sells a curry plant for 150 rupees, a plant of athugoa, cherry tomato etc. for 100 rupees, a Dubai pumpkin plant for 60 rupees, a gourd, a bitter gourd, a chilli plant, an eggplant plant for 45 rupees and a chilli plant for 40 rupees.",
        "When we asked a plant nursery in Kegalle, they said that this plant is sold at a price of 35 rupees.",
        "These days, plant nurseries say that this situation is due to the increase in the demand for plants due to the increase in the demand of plants due to the people living in the suburbs of their homes or resorting to cultivation activities.",
        "The price of vegetable plants in the areas where cultivation is done outside the city is quite low, and when we asked two plant nurseries in Kurunegala, Kobeigane and Wattala area, they said that they sell a plant at prices between 10 and 25 rupees.",
        "A vegetable plant is sold at prices between 12 and 22 rupees at the plant nursery in Kobeigan, while the price of 10 plants at the Wattala plant nursery is 150 rupees.",
        "People who buy plants for growing in gardens say that in the past, a collection of 10 or 15 chillies and vegetables could be bought at a price of 50 rupees, but now it costs 100 rupees to buy a plant.",
        "They mention that because some plants die after planting and the prices of fertilizers have also increased, it is not easy to grow them in the gardens."
      ],
